00:18:41,181 --> 00:18:49,441
being close to the dock. But I would say roughly - give or
take a week or two - about... two years!

199
00:18:49,738 --> 00:18:53,631
- Two years?
- Yeah, give or take a week or two!

200
00:18:53,988 --> 00:19:01,567
If you think I'm staying in a lead-lined nissan hut with you
and Grandad and a chemical khazi you've got another think coming.

201
00:19:02,027 --> 00:19:05,905
Yeah, but if we leave the shelter within two years we'd
die of radiation poisoning!

202
00:19:06,147 --> 00:19:10,230
And if we stay inside the shelter for two years we'll
die of bloody lead poisoning.

203
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:15,548
He's right Rodney. The rescue team will whip us straight
round the nearest scrap metal yard!

204
00:19:16,467 --> 00:19:21,131
Yeah, that's another point, that's a point. Listen, oi!
These batteries are supposed to purify the air right,

205
00:19:21,324 --> 00:19:25,938
they last 12 hours, right?
Okay how many of them are we gonna need?

206
00:19:26,258 --> 00:19:29,157
Come on Einstein, you're the one with the GCE in Maths!

207
00:19:29,841 --> 00:19:34,985
Well, it's two a day, seven
days a week two sevens are 14.

208
00:19:35,321 --> 00:19:38,551
See that Grandad - two sevens
are 14. Just like that, no hesitation.

209
00:19:39,262 --> 00:19:44,265
Shut up will yer! So that's 14
times 52...

210
00:19:44,499 --> 00:19:51,941
- Twice!
- I know! So that works out at about 1450-odd.

211
00:19:53,754 --> 00:20:02,374
Well, that's not too bad, I thought we were gonna need a
lot! What we're gonna need is 1450-odd heavy duty batteries,

212
00:20:02,603 --> 00:20:07,525
about five ton of canned food,
30,000 gallons of fresh drinking water,

213
00:20:07,725 --> 00:20:10,631
and a three and 'arf acre warehouse
to store it all in!

214
00:20:10,666 --> 00:20:15,653
Well I did say we'd have to
iron out a few little wrinkles, didn't I?

215
00:20:15,873 --> 00:20:21,162
Few little wrinkles? A few little wrinkles? We've got
more wrinkles than a elephant's got in his bleedin' trunk!

216
00:20:23,130 --> 00:20:29,150
All in all, and taking every thing in consideration Rodney,
I think I would rather be outside and go instantly with the bomb!

217
00:20:29,513 --> 00:20:36,074
Instantly eh? And what makes you so sure it'd ne instant eh Del?
Them bombs contain Strontium 90 not Nescafe!

218
00:20:37,254 --> 00:20:41,556
You see the bomb explodes bout a mile above the city right,
causing a radioactive rain to fall.

219
00:20:41,805 --> 00:20:46,497
Now this radiation then penetrates the pores of the
skin causing violent sores and diseases.

220
00:20:47,087 --> 00:20:49,090
Um, best not to wear anything
decent then eh?

221
00:20:49,861 --> 00:20:55,671
Will you be serious for one minute. Look, it's here once
the radiation is in the blood stream

222
00:20:55,865 --> 00:21:02,490
it begins to attack your metabolism. You'll become subject
to drastic biological changes, that's metamorphosis!

223
00:21:06,393 --> 00:21:11,024
Yeah anyway, your shape and form will alter radically as
the mutation takes effect!

224
00:21:11,402 --> 00:21:17,820
Don't sound too promising do it Del Boy, I mean you have a
job to get a suit off the peg now don't yer!

225
00:21:19,739 --> 00:21:25,371
Alright, alright, you can laugh, but I'm telling you,
this city would be inhabited by roaming mobs of mutants!

226
00:21:26,075 --> 00:21:31,838
Vacant eyed sub-humans dragging their knuckles through the
litter and debris that was once civilization.

227
00:21:32,497 --> 00:21:37,162
Sounds a bit like Stamford Bridge after a bad result...
Look if this is true Rodney

228
00:21:37,832 --> 00:21:40,744
what the hell are we doing
trying to survive?

229
00:21:41,024 --> 00:21:45,876
Well, it's our duty ain't it, I mean when we step out of here
we're gonna be intact, perfect.

230
00:21:49,528 --> 00:21:54,696
Yeah, well I mean you know, the human race will be
looking to people like us to replenish the species,

231
00:21:55,001 --> 00:21:58,349
we'll be like two new Adams going
forth to multiply.

232
00:22:01,366 --> 00:22:05,605
Yeah! And you, you dirty little ram, will be out there
multiplying quicker than a pocket calculator!

233
00:22:06,564 --> 00:22:12,287
I see it all now, he's practically praying
for the end of civilization just so he can get out there

234
00:22:12,497 --> 00:22:16,275
and put it about a bit! What time do you
make it Rodney?

235
00:22:16,642 --> 00:22:18,019
Ten past 12.

236
00:22:18,269 --> 00:22:20,713
Oh yeah, I make it that too. C'mon then Grandad it's
bedtime, come on.

237
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:25,411
Well, as the saying goes, if my species needs me I will not
be found wanting.

238
00:22:28,114 --> 00:22:30,513
Yeah, anyway that's one thing
to look forward to innit Grandad, eh?

239
00:22:31,154 --> 00:22:35,558
You know, come the end of the war me and Rodney
are gonna make a foursome with a couple of mutants!

240
00:22:36,957 --> 00:22:41,936
I'll have one with three lug 'oles and the eye
underneath her arm, 'cos I don't fancy yours much!

241
00:22:42,801 --> 00:22:44,361
It won't be like that!!!

242
00:22:44,570 --> 00:22:48,053
You bet your sweet bippy it won't! It won't make any
difference to you anyway,

243
00:22:48,344 --> 00:22:53,356
you go out with mutants in peacetime! I mean look at
that thing you took out on Thursday!

244
00:22:53,547 --> 00:22:57,921
Cor, stroll on, I was so embarrassed I had to
tell my mates you were taking it to market!

245
00:22:58,870 --> 00:23:00,821
I did try and warn you it was
a bit ragged!

246
00:23:01,018 --> 00:23:06,144
Bit ragged! You liar! You said
to me it looked like the one out of Abba!

247
00:23:07,462 --> 00:23:13,548
Yes, I meant the one with the beard, anyway we won't be the
only ones to survive the holocaust intact, will we?

248
00:23:13,957 --> 00:23:17,828
I mean I'm thinking of the various institutions -
public schools, that sort of thing.

249
00:23:18,456 --> 00:23:20,715
I mean you bet your life
Rodney’s got a shelter.

250
00:23:22,079 --> 00:23:29,294
Eh Del? A thousand nubile girls - in a shelter...in
school uniform!

251
00:23:32,336 --> 00:23:34,156
You sicko!

252
00:23:34,769 --> 00:23:39,086
No, no, don't misunderstand me. I mean the school uniforms
are of no importance whatsoever.

253
00:23:39,268 --> 00:23:40,669
I don't know why I mentioned
them.

254
00:23:40,851 --> 00:23:44,305
No, no, it's probably because you're a twisted perverted
corrupted, warped little pervo!

255
00:23:45,673 --> 00:23:49,745
Well, yeah, that might have something to do with it!
It's in the line of duty Del!

256
00:23:50,027 --> 00:23:52,853
They're perfect specimens.
They're intelligent.

257
00:23:53,235 --> 00:23:55,394
Course they're intelligent,
they're still at bloody school ain't they?

258
00:23:56,562 --> 00:24:02,401
They're fit - all that hockey!
You might fancy the headmistress!

259
00:24:02,733 --> 00:24:04,495
Oh thank you very much.

260
00:24:06,641 --> 00:24:10,191
Well, I think it's definitely
worth bearing in mind. In an emergency.

261
00:24:15,981 --> 00:24:18,245
- Yeah alright, well, goodnight Rodney.
- Goodnight Del.

262
00:24:23,507 --> 00:24:26,270
- Night Grandad.
- Goodnight Rodney.

263
00:24:28,306 --> 00:24:30,653
- Night John Boy.
- Shut up.

264
00:24:45,203 --> 00:24:52,835
- War is hell!!
- What?

265
00:24:54,216 --> 00:24:58,962
- War is hell! Alan Ladd said that.
- Did he really? Go to sleep.

266
00:25:02,445 --> 00:25:07,200
- Or was it Audie Murphy?
- I dunno, I'm tired.

267
00:25:10,186 --> 00:25:11,813
It must have been one of 'em!

268
00:25:12,022 --> 00:25:15,684
Well perhaps they both bloody
said it! Now go to sleep will you.

269
00:25:19,241 --> 00:25:20,446
No, that was Rock Hudson!

270
00:25:20,795 --> 00:25:24,360
For crying out loud, will you two go to sleep.

271
00:25:32,895 --> 00:25:40,197
Rodney...Here Rodney
don't keep yer eyes closed - I'm talking to you!

272
00:25:40,762 --> 00:25:41,741
What?

273
00:25:41,973 --> 00:25:46,621
I've just been thinking. Might not be a bad idea to survive
the next war after all!

274
00:25:47,190 --> 00:25:48,920
Why? You got something up yer
sleeve Del?

275
00:25:49,096 --> 00:25:51,952
No, no, just a little idea that's been running round in
me old brain box, that's all.

276
00:25:52,227 --> 00:25:59,926
What's the point? All the animals will be dead. Won't be
able to grow nothing 'cos all the earth'll be contaminated!

277
00:26:01,020 --> 00:26:03,609
Where we gonna get something
to eat?

278
00:26:04,336 --> 00:26:12,220
Bound to be  little Paki shop open somewhere! But we won't
be the only ones to survive will we?

279
00:26:12,382 --> 00:26:15,897
I was just thinking
about all them girls down at that Roedean School.

280
00:26:16,857 --> 00:26:21,732
No, no, no, no, nothing like that, nothing like that. I was
just thinking you see, most of those girls down there,

281
00:26:21,890 --> 00:26:23,832
they are daughters of the noblesses!

282
00:26:26,034 --> 00:26:27,069
The what Del?

283
00:26:27,263 --> 00:26:33,141
The noblesse, the noblesses.
It's French for nobility ain't it eh?

284
00:26:33,831 --> 00:26:35,547
Oh sorry - I was miles off.

285
00:26:37,681 --> 00:26:41,902
Well you see, down there you don't know who's who, do you?
I mean you could meet a scruffy 17-year-old

286
00:26:42,093 --> 00:26:48,491
in a sweaty hockey shirt and muddy plimsoles,
and you could be talking to the 459th in line

287
00:26:48,629 --> 00:26:55,811
for the throne! But after the old Russians have dropped 20
thousand nuclear bombs on us that scruffy 17-year-old

288
00:26:56,720 --> 00:27:02,082
could turn out to be the first in line for the throne.
So, you see, if I got on my bike,

289
00:27:03,566 --> 00:27:09,075
nip down there a bit sharpish like, did me Adams act -
splash of Brut, you know, took her out for a steak meal -

290
00:27:10,361 --> 00:27:18,341
loads of charm - I could end up being the King!
On the other hand a bit of mutation,

291
00:27:18,555 --> 00:27:25,916
a touch of Strontium 90, I could end up being the
Queen. But either way, either way,

292
00:27:26,087 --> 00:27:29,517
see it wouldn't matter because the taxman wouldn't be
able to get at me, would he, eh?

293
00:27:29,685 --> 00:27:36,362
Because I would be the head of State. And what with
you out there multiplying all over the place,

294
00:27:36,802 --> 00:27:39,167
I shouldn't be short of a few subjects,
should I, eh?

295
00:27:43,398 --> 00:27:46,204
We, we could go for our
holidays in Mustique.

296
00:27:47,859 --> 00:27:50,549
- What? What?
- Grandad could be the Queen Mother!

297
00:27:54,627 --> 00:28:05,587
Yeah, we'll dye his hat pink... yeah, yeah. No even if that
didn't happen and I can't honestly see how I could fail.

298
00:28:06,794 --> 00:28:13,249
You see if the entire civilization was wiped out
we'd all be equal wouldn't we,

299
00:28:13,792 --> 00:28:16,061
'cos none of us would have
nothing, right.

300
00:28:16,413 --> 00:28:19,322
- Right!
- Except us Rodney!

301
00:28:21,164 --> 00:28:23,185
Well what would we have Del?

302
00:28:23,435 --> 00:28:29,099
A grands worth of lead eh...
pretty shrewd, eh Rodney?

303
00:28:29,444 --> 00:28:32,041
Yeah, that's a real mindbender
Del, that!

304
00:28:33,869 --> 00:28:40,934
No, no, we'll be alright. We'll survive Rodney,
d'you know why? Because we're survivors that's why.

305
00:28:43,630 --> 00:28:49,083
When did the alarm bells start ringing and the missiles start
firing, and all the people are rushing about

306
00:28:49,285 --> 00:28:55,988
like mad mice trying to find somewhere to hide,
we'll be tucked up in our own little nuclear shelter.

307
00:28:58,963 --> 00:29:05,537
The end of the world could be just the break we're
looking for! Oh we're pretty shrewd Rodney.

308
00:29:06,403 --> 00:29:13,951
If they started dropping the bomb on us right now
we'd be as safe as houses brother, safe as houses!

309
